{
  "texts": [
    "It is in this space that government regulation of AI makes sense to us.",
    "Others have made claims in the name of ethics about regulating characteristics of AI; however, these suggestions seem outdated.",
    "According to Bryson (2010), robots should be \"slaves\"-this does not mean that we should make robots slaves, but rather, we should keep them at a simpler developmental level by not giving them characteristics that might enable people to view them as anything other than owned and created by humans for humans.",
    "Bryson claims that it would be immoral to create a robot that can feel emotions like pain.",
    "Metzinger (2021) called for a ban on development of AI that could be considered sentient."
  ]
}